19
00:00:18,356 --> 00:00:20,107
<i>A darkness awakes!</i>

20
00:00:20,149 --> 00:00:24,278
<i>Count Dooku's bitter betrayal of
his former apprentice, Asajj Ventress,</i>

21
00:00:24,403 --> 00:00:29,534
<i>resulted in the creation of a new menace
in the galaxy, Savage Opress.</i>

22
00:00:29,784 --> 00:00:33,037
<i>Caught in a deadly game of revenge
between Ventress and Dooku,</i>

23
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:35,373
<i>Savage barely escaped the carnage.</i>

24
00:00:35,456 --> 00:00:38,459
<i>Beaten and alone he returned
to Mother Talzin,</i>

25
00:00:38,584 --> 00:00:44,048
<i>his creator, who gave him a new quest
to pursue his long-lost brother.</i>

26
00:00:46,968 --> 00:00:49,679
I can sense him, Grievous.

27
00:00:50,304 --> 00:00:56,352
That creature, Savage Opress,
is growing stronger and stronger

28
00:00:56,435 --> 00:00:58,646
as each day passes.

29
00:00:59,313 --> 00:01:03,150
You consider him a threat?

30
00:01:03,818 --> 00:01:05,945
He is a threat to all of us!

31
00:01:05,987 --> 00:01:07,572
Even the Jedi!

32
00:01:07,655 --> 00:01:12,868
With the Night sisters eradicated,
there is no one left to control him.

33
00:01:13,327 --> 00:01:18,124
Something is rising, something sinister.

34
00:01:29,719 --> 00:01:30,928
He's choking her.

35
00:01:31,012 --> 00:01:32,430
-Hey!
-Let her go!

36
00:01:35,057 --> 00:01:36,726
He's choking her.

37
00:01:39,270 --> 00:01:41,689
Hurry up! Call the authorities!

38
00:01:52,575 --> 00:01:57,371
Mother Talzin, this dust,

39
00:01:59,582 --> 00:02:01,042
it's a clue.

40
00:02:07,256 --> 00:02:12,887
Yes, Savage, you are getting
closer and closer.

41
00:02:13,304 --> 00:02:18,225
Soon you and your brother will be reunited.

42
00:02:18,726 --> 00:02:22,188
I must make the necessary preparations.

43
00:02:23,022 --> 00:02:26,484
So he hands me a blaster
about a fourth the size...

44
00:02:26,567 --> 00:02:27,735
Cheers.

45
00:02:29,236 --> 00:02:32,615
- Why so tense?
- I'm not sure.

46
00:02:33,658 --> 00:02:37,244
I thought I sensed someone from my past.

47
00:02:38,329 --> 00:02:40,081
Who is this someone?

48
00:02:41,582 --> 00:02:43,084
A monster.

49
00:03:15,866 --> 00:03:19,954
Huh. Hey! What are you doing here?
Get outta here! I'm about to take off!

50
00:03:20,037 --> 00:03:24,500
The cargo you just dropped off,
what planet did it come from?

51
00:03:24,959 --> 00:03:28,045
The junk fields on planet Lotho Minor!

52
00:03:28,129 --> 00:03:30,464
-Take me there.
-Okay! Okay!

53
00:03:38,097 --> 00:03:40,474
Uh, shouldn't we be getting
back to the cruiser?

54
00:03:40,558 --> 00:03:44,019
Nah, I'm hungry and tired of
those government rations.

55
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:46,981
Hey, looks like trouble. Come on.

56
00:03:52,611 --> 00:03:54,447
Hey, what are you doing?

57
00:03:54,572 --> 00:03:57,199
We don't want any trouble.
We were only trying to help.

58
00:03:57,324 --> 00:04:00,661
Lou ! Are you crazy?
Pointing that thing at a Jedi?

59
00:04:00,828 --> 00:04:02,621
Put it down now!

60
00:04:03,038 --> 00:04:06,917
I'm sorry, sir. I'm just all shook up.

61
00:04:07,668 --> 00:04:10,254
I understand. You want to tell me
what happened here?

62
00:04:10,337 --> 00:04:12,131
We have it under control, sir.

63
00:04:12,173 --> 00:04:16,010
It looks like only a simple altercation.
Happens here all the time.

64
00:04:16,051 --> 00:04:19,722
He's telling the truth.
We get some rough characters in here.

65
00:04:19,805 --> 00:04:22,516
Things like this happen too often to count.

66
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:25,186
Why don't you and your friend
take a load off?

67
00:04:25,269 --> 00:04:28,272
I'll get you some food. Meal's on the house.

68
00:04:34,987 --> 00:04:37,406
You're not gonna kill me, are you?

69
00:04:51,462 --> 00:04:52,671
Master?

70
00:04:53,672 --> 00:04:54,882
Anakin?

71
00:04:56,133 --> 00:05:01,722
I sense a disturbance. Something sinister.

72
00:05:02,890 --> 00:05:04,642
All the way out here?

73
00:05:05,309 --> 00:05:06,435
Yes.

74
00:05:07,436 --> 00:05:10,564
Do you know what, or who, it is?

75
00:05:11,232 --> 00:05:15,653
No,
but whatever it is, it feels familiar.

76
00:05:20,199 --> 00:05:24,537
Just my luck, I got to go back
to that scrap pile floating in space.

77
00:05:24,662 --> 00:05:26,330
Just get moving.

78
00:05:26,413 --> 00:05:29,625
Fine, I guess things could be worse.

79
00:05:29,708 --> 00:05:31,669
Though I'm not sure how.

80
00:05:56,110 --> 00:05:57,611
He is close.

81
00:06:21,176 --> 00:06:23,596
-Get out. Now!
-No. Come on!

82
00:06:34,148 --> 00:06:36,567
I'm here at last, brother.

83
00:07:37,878 --> 00:07:41,882
No, no, not when I'm so close!

84
00:07:54,228 --> 00:07:55,688
Hey! Big guy!

85
00:07:55,938 --> 00:07:58,440
I don't have time for you!

86
00:07:58,524 --> 00:07:59,817
Over here!

87
00:08:05,072 --> 00:08:06,907
You trackin' somebody?

88
00:08:07,116 --> 00:08:09,034
What do you know about it?

89
00:08:09,827 --> 00:08:11,620
I'm... I'm Morley.

90
00:08:11,954 --> 00:08:13,622
I could help you!

91
00:08:14,832 --> 00:08:16,542
We've got everything here!

92
00:08:16,583 --> 00:08:21,422
I can get you what you want,
for the right amount, of course.

93
00:08:25,592 --> 00:08:31,098
I mean, it'd be my payment-free
pleasure, of course!

94
00:08:32,307 --> 00:08:34,685
I think I can manage on my own.

95
00:08:38,647 --> 00:08:42,109
Show me something,
show me which way to go!

96
00:08:44,445 --> 00:08:46,947
What you need is a guide!

97
00:08:47,322 --> 00:08:49,324
Leave me alone!

98
00:08:49,867 --> 00:08:51,118
Wait!

99
00:08:52,786 --> 00:08:56,707
Trust me! Not everything
on this planet is junk.

100
00:08:57,416 --> 00:08:58,667
It's not?

101
00:08:59,376 --> 00:09:01,295
There are things like me.

102
00:09:01,378 --> 00:09:03,839
Things that live and breathe.

103
00:09:04,298 --> 00:09:08,260
Perhaps you're looking for something
more like that.

104
00:09:08,302 --> 00:09:09,595
Show me.

105
00:09:10,137 --> 00:09:12,514
You're already heading
in the right direction,

106
00:09:12,598 --> 00:09:16,268
even though your
handy doo-da there isn't working.

107
00:09:16,977 --> 00:09:21,356
But you'll need my guidance to
avoid the fire-breathers.

108
00:09:23,442 --> 00:09:24,985
Fire-breathers?

109
00:09:37,998 --> 00:09:41,835
Yep. Fire-breathers.
They'll getcha! Follow me!

110
00:10:17,121 --> 00:10:18,247
Ah!

111
00:10:18,455 --> 00:10:22,000
The Junkers. Junkers strange folk.

112
00:10:22,668 --> 00:10:25,045
Yeah, looks like it.

113
00:10:27,589 --> 00:10:29,550
We better get outta here.

114
00:10:30,092 --> 00:10:32,344
They can get a little cranky.

115
00:10:44,940 --> 00:10:47,568
Big guy, we really should go.

116
00:10:50,237 --> 00:10:51,572
A fight?

117
00:11:33,906 --> 00:11:34,990
Wow!

118
00:11:41,205 --> 00:11:42,456
Let's go.

119
00:11:43,999 --> 00:11:47,085
So, who are you looking for?

120
00:11:50,297 --> 00:11:52,132
Come on.

121
00:11:52,299 --> 00:11:55,093
My brother. I've been searching for him.

122
00:11:55,969 --> 00:11:59,139
Uh... Does he look like you?

123
00:11:59,598 --> 00:12:01,266
Have you seen him?

124
00:12:01,558 --> 00:12:06,438
No. No. I just heard stories
about a horned man.

125
00:12:07,314 --> 00:12:10,484
I thought it was just an old local legend.

126
00:12:10,943 --> 00:12:12,319
How old?

127
00:12:13,111 --> 00:12:14,321
Old.

128
00:12:16,823 --> 00:12:21,662
They say he drags things down beneath

129
00:12:22,246 --> 00:12:24,790
and they never come back up.

130
00:12:25,999 --> 00:12:28,502
Oh, but it's only a legend, like I said.

131
00:12:37,469 --> 00:12:38,804
Acid rain.

132
00:12:39,846 --> 00:12:43,016
It'll melt us down
if we don't find shelter soon.

133
00:12:46,979 --> 00:12:48,355
Over there.

134
00:12:54,778 --> 00:12:56,029
Oh, oh, oh...

135
00:12:56,113 --> 00:12:57,489
What the...

136
00:13:12,963 --> 00:13:14,673
This is it.

137
00:13:25,976 --> 00:13:29,062
It doesn't look like anyone's here, big guy.

138
00:13:29,938 --> 00:13:31,648
I can see that!

139
00:13:40,699 --> 00:13:44,244
Mother Talzin ! She betrayed me!

140
00:13:44,328 --> 00:13:46,330
My brother must be dead!

141
00:13:54,755 --> 00:13:57,591
She's not the only one who betrayed you!

142
00:14:00,260 --> 00:14:02,220
You'll make a good offering

143
00:14:02,262 --> 00:14:06,558
and when my master's finished with you,
I get the leftovers!

144
00:14:23,325 --> 00:14:25,243
Brother? Is that you, brother?

145
00:15:24,010 --> 00:15:25,178
Is that you, brother?

146
00:15:45,824 --> 00:15:46,825
You!

147
00:15:49,244 --> 00:15:52,122
Stop there! What have you done
with my brother?

148
00:15:52,205 --> 00:15:54,040
Answer me, you monster!

149
00:16:20,275 --> 00:16:23,445
What? It can't be.

150
00:16:28,033 --> 00:16:30,160
-Brother!
-No!

151
00:16:32,746 --> 00:16:34,247
Wait, brother!

152
00:16:36,666 --> 00:16:38,418
No! No!

153
00:16:49,596 --> 00:16:52,849
No! No! No!

154
00:16:52,933 --> 00:16:55,435
You are the brother I've been searching for.

155
00:16:55,519 --> 00:17:00,357
No! No! No! No! No!

156
00:17:00,941 --> 00:17:03,944
Yes! We are, we are brothers.

157
00:17:04,069 --> 00:17:05,278
No!

158
00:17:07,113 --> 00:17:09,324
You... You don't know!

159
00:17:09,866 --> 00:17:12,202
You don't know anything!

160
00:17:14,120 --> 00:17:16,289
Never, never!

161
00:17:16,915 --> 00:17:18,959
I know I am your blood!

162
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:20,168
Never!

163
00:17:21,628 --> 00:17:23,463
Never, never!

164
00:17:31,304 --> 00:17:33,807
I'm ready for my leftovers.

165
00:17:35,058 --> 00:17:37,185
Oh ! You're still alive, huh?

166
00:17:39,896 --> 00:17:42,065
- Who did this to my brother?
- No.

167
00:17:42,148 --> 00:17:43,817
Are you part of this?

168
00:17:44,484 --> 00:17:45,569
No.

169
00:17:46,194 --> 00:17:49,364
No. No. I found him this way.

170
00:17:50,073 --> 00:17:52,909
It wasn't me. I found him this way.

171
00:17:52,993 --> 00:17:56,246
You can't be trusted.
You're a slithering liar!

172
00:17:56,329 --> 00:17:57,872
You should have been helping him!

173
00:17:57,998 --> 00:18:02,168
I didn't know! I didn't know!

174
00:18:09,301 --> 00:18:11,386
This is where you live?

175
00:18:14,347 --> 00:18:16,349
How long have you been here?

176
00:18:16,850 --> 00:18:19,019
Years and years and years.

177
00:18:19,936 --> 00:18:25,025
Through victory, my chains are broken.
The chains, the chains are the easy part.

178
00:18:25,150 --> 00:18:29,321
It's what goes on in here that's hard.

179
00:18:31,197 --> 00:18:33,450
You have been lost, my brother.

180
00:18:33,575 --> 00:18:35,702
Do you remember who you are?

181
00:18:35,952 --> 00:18:37,704
Where you came from?

182
00:18:38,038 --> 00:18:43,084
Always remember I am fear,
always remember I am hunter,

183
00:18:43,209 --> 00:18:48,465
always remember I am filth,
always remember I am nothing.

184
00:18:51,051 --> 00:18:52,385
Your legs...

185
00:18:52,802 --> 00:18:56,890
That scum, he took them from me.
He took them!

186
00:18:57,182 --> 00:18:58,892
Who? Who took them?

187
00:18:59,267 --> 00:19:02,812
Jedi. Jedi.

188
00:19:04,606 --> 00:19:06,733
-You remember?
-I don't ask for mercy, Master.

189
00:19:06,816 --> 00:19:10,820
Mercy is a lie, a delusion of the weak
to think themselves strong.

190
00:19:10,987 --> 00:19:13,740
-I ask not for mercy...
-What? What is it?

191
00:19:13,823 --> 00:19:15,909
-But the chance...
-Brother, what are you saying?

192
00:19:16,910 --> 00:19:21,414
And through the filth,
through the grief, Jedi!

193
00:19:22,832 --> 00:19:24,292
Revenge.

194
00:19:25,627 --> 00:19:27,754
I must have revenge.

195
00:19:38,515 --> 00:19:39,974
Master Yoda?

196
00:19:40,725 --> 00:19:43,978
Feel the disturbance in the Force, do you?

197
00:19:44,437 --> 00:19:45,814
Yes, Master.

198
00:19:46,940 --> 00:19:49,150
Fear you are in danger, I do.

199
00:19:49,901 --> 00:19:55,281
From the dead, an old enemy
has awakened seeking vengeance.

200
00:19:56,074 --> 00:19:57,575
An old enemy?

201
00:19:58,076 --> 00:20:01,454
Killed your master many moons ago,
he did.

202
00:20:02,747 --> 00:20:05,917
How can this be? I killed him myself!

203
00:20:06,626 --> 00:20:08,294
It is so, I fear.

204
00:20:10,130 --> 00:20:12,632
Darth Maul alive?

205
00:20:12,656 --> 00:20:17,656
http://hiqve.com/

